               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440205-name-1569" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1569" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1569" type="surname" value="PEARSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1569" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM PEARSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am servant to Mr. James Gale, who keeps the Hen and Chickens at Walworth-common. This quart pot is his—I was going round for my pots last Friday morning, between nine and ten o'clock—I saw the prisoner pass, facing me, and he <hi rend="italic">chucked</hi> a bag on his back—I ran and caught him, and asked what he had got in the bag—he said, "Nothing"—I took the bag off his back, and shook this pot out, and asked where he got it—he said a boy gave it him to carry—it had been at a customer's honse—I had seen it safe at my master's on Thursday night.</p>
